entry.title: Psoropempula erythrostethus
entry.content: Spotted patrolling the same area as the Zebra Spider Wasp in observation 8828. ID by Ken Walker. At least half the size. This species also depicted at http://lifeunseen.com/index2_item_5399.php

entry.title: Turneromyia bassiana
entry.content: Great watching this - tapping with its tail at the covered entrance to the hole. Not sure if tapping was at its home or trying to encourage a spider out of its hole. Otherwise it was flying/patrolling low across the forest floor searching for spiders.
